\par\par \b \uc2 Businesses want CGI to help fix investment climate   \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 443 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 December 2003\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2003 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Business communities urged the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) to push the government to focus immediately on improving the country's investment climate in order to attain sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.   \par \par \uc2 National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee (KPEN) chairman Sofjan Wanandi told The Jakarta Post that it was now imperative for the CGI and the government to fix the investment climate, encouraging the real sector to drive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery.   \par \par \uc2 "We want the CGI and the government to focus on improving our unfavorable investment climate so that our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will not depend anymore on a consumer-driven base, which is unsustainable," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Sofjan and other business representatives made the requests on Wednesday during a luncheon with CGI representatives and several high-ranking government officials.   \par \par \uc2 Aside from Sofjan, who was representing the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin), other representatives included those from the International Business Chamber (IBC), the Jakarta Japan Club Foundation (JJCF) and the American Chamber of Commerce in Indonesia (AmCham).   \par \par \uc2 Officials of the country's traditional donor grouping met here for a two-day annual gathering to decide on a new loan commitment to help finance the 2004 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 During the luncheon, business representatives launched several key issues that had long been denting the confidence of foreign investors from entering the country.   \par \par \uc2 Kadin, for example, raised a key labor issue, emphasizing the increasing difficulties companies experienced in dealing with labor, and the inability of the government -- particularly the Ministry of Manpower and Transmigration -- to function as a neutral arbiter in labor disputes.   \par \par \uc2 Kadin also raised concerns over the government's labor policies, some of which it considered irrational.   \par \par \uc2 The IBC expressed its concerns over the need for legal reform, as the weak legal system had created business \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 It also complained about the lack of adequate infrastructure to support business activities.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the JJCF focused on \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and customs administration. One of the points it raised was the lack of transparency in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regulations, which had created confusion among taxpayers and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collectors in complying with the regulations.   \par \par \uc2 Other issues raised by JJCF was the need for improved efficiency in customs clearance, reducing smuggling in the import and export sectors and comprehensive control and coordination among government agencies in clearance services.   \par \par \uc2 AmCham raised issues in the mining and energy sector, stressing the lack of competitive policies.   \par \par \uc2 Investment activities in the country have weakened since the late 1990s financial crisis. Without higher investment performance, the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could not grow by between 6-7 percent, a level deemed necessary to help resolve the huge unemployment problem.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020031210dzcb00015\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
