onsible for damage to Indonesia's forest resources.   \par \par \uc2 While acknowledging concerns over environmental degradation, Dorodjatun said mining areas would only take up 2 percent of total protected forest areas, which currently stand at 11.4 million hectares.   \par \par \uc2 Dorodjatun said new mining activities should start within 10 to 20 years to take advantage of the rising price of mining commodities spurred by high demand from China's rapid manufacturing industry.   \par \par \uc2 "If we start new mining investment after 20 years, it will be too late because by then China may be slowing down and has less demand," he claimed.   \par \par \uc2 The mining sector has been in the doldrums for years due to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in government mining \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , high \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , lack of security guarantees, corruption and inconsistencies related to regional autonomy. These have discouraged existing mining companies and potential investors.   \par \par \uc2 The country is slipping off the stage of the world's mining industry in terms of attractiveness for investment. The Indonesian Mining Association (IMA) said Indonesia was ranked 27 out of 35 countries surveyed between 2001 to 2002.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020031216dzch00014\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
