\par\par \b \uc2 Govt moves ahead with FTZ bill, says Minister   \b0\par\par\uc2 Fadli and Dadan Wijaksana, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta/Batam   \par \uc2 525 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 January 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The government remains committed to the deliberation of a bill to grant Batam free trade zone (FTZ) status, despite the recent imposition of a decree taxing certain products on the industrial island, a top \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister said.   \par \par \uc2 The implementation of a value added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) and a luxury goods \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on products designed for domestic consumption would not affect the ongoing deliberation at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the FTZ bill, Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said on Monday.   \par \par \uc2 "But, we have to understand that this is a \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  process in which we have to cooperate with lawmakers. So, definitely it will take some time (to complete the deliberations)," said Dorodjatun.   \par \par \uc2 He was responding to questions on the impacts of the issuance of the presidential decree on Batam \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  relative to the Batam FTZ bill, which the government and the House have been discussing for over four months.   \par \par \uc2 The presidential decree stipulates that, effective Jan. 1, cigarette, liquor and automotive products will be subject to VAT as well as a luxury \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Electronic products will follow starting in March.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 , first proposed by the Ministry of Finance in 1998, is imposed only on the products designed for domestic the market and not for exports. Analysts say this is contradictory to an FTZ status which will abolish automatically the need to apply differential \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  treatment to domestic and export transactions.   \par \par \uc2 When asked whether the government would revoke the presidential decree once Batam is granted FTZ status, Dorodjatun did not provide a clear-cut answer.   \par \par \uc2 "In principle, the \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  are being imposed in every part of the country no matter where you live. For an area holding an FTZ status, such a ruling would still be applied as well, although adjustments will be made," he said, without elaborating.   \par \par \uc2 The implementation of the two \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  is to correct a misguided \b \highlight22\uc2 tax policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  measure imposed on the island, since it was declared an industrial bonded zone in 1978 -- which allows export-oriented firms to bring in capital goods and raw materials without paying import duties, VAT or other indirect \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  normally imposed on trading transactions in other parts of the country.   \par \par \uc2 However, over time, the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  exemption \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been enjoyed not only by export-related products, but also those for domestic sales.   \par \par \uc2 This prompted the finance ministry six years ago to reimpose the VAT on Batam to raise revenues.   \par \par \uc2 Batam-based companies have voiced strong opposition to the new ruling, saying it would only create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  among investors and shatter their appetite to invest in the island.   \par \par \uc2 David Octarevia, head of the island's business association which groups together dozens of businesses operating there, was one of the strong opponents to the new ruling.   \par \par \uc2 "This will badly hurt not only business people, but also the whole community. We're considering asking the Constitutional Court to annul the decree," he said.   \par \par \uc2 "It's hard to accept this \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We have to make plenty of adjustments because of this," echoed Ismeth Abdullah, chairman of Batam Industrial Development Authority (BIDA).   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040105e0160001b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
