\par\par \b \uc2 Tourism prepares for the doldrums   \b0\par\par\uc2 P.C. Naommy, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 529 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 January 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Tourism industry players lamented on Tuesday that the new visa-on-arrival \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VOA), effective Feb. 1, would hinder the government's foreign exchange target of US$500 billion from the tourism sector this year.   \par \par \uc2 "The target is nonsense," said IB Lolec, president of Pacific World Nusantara, whose core business is travel and transportation. He was speaking at a seminar on "The Dynamics of Indonesia's Tourism, an Outlook in 2004," held by the University of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Social Research Institute (LPEM-UI).   \par \par \uc2 Lolec said the government was unrealistic in setting such a high target, especially with the new VOA \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 He also said that familiarizing immigration and airport officials with the new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was poor, and this lack of preparation and proper training would lead to long lines and delays in processing tourists on their arrival.   \par \par \uc2 Ranier Daulaw, owner of the Marin Tur Travel Biro, who also attended the seminar, expressed his frustration over the inconsistency of the VOA \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as many potential customers had canceled their tours over the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "We will accept and support the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  even if it hurts the tourism business in Indonesia, but please do not be wishy-washy about the implementation date," Ranier said.   \par \par \uc2 He also told The Jakarta Post that the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  date of enactment and lack of socialization of the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  proved that it had not been well prepared, and had thus diminished the trust of foreign travelers.   \par \par \uc2 The VOA \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was issued by the Ministry of Justice and Human Rights late last year. The \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grants a visa-free facility to tourists who are citizens from countries which also provide similar facility to Indonesian citizens.   \par \par \uc2 Tourists who are nationals from the United States, Australia, South Africa, Argentina, Brazil, Denmark, the United Arab Emirates, Finland, Hungary, the United Kingdom, Italy, Japan, Germany, Canada, South Korea, Norway or France are eligible for the visa-on-arrival facility from Indonesia. Citizens of Taiwan are also granted the same facility.   \par \par \uc2 The new \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  cuts the length of the free-visa-on-arrival stay from 60 days to 30 days. The new visa-on-arrival would also only allow visitors to stay here for 30 days.   \par \par \uc2 The seminar, which was opened by keynote speaker Sultan Hamengkubuwono X, also featured a paper on Indonesian tourism based on research by Ringoringo Achmadi from LPEM-UI. The paper makes several recommendations for boosting the tourism sector, including placing the Ministry of Tourism and Culture under the Office of the Coordinating Minister of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "Tourism is not only about culture, but also about business," said Ringoringo.   \par \par \uc2 Udin Saifuddin, marketing deputy at the Ministry of Tourism and Culture, said the government and tourism industry would have to make concerted efforts to reach this year's target of five million visitors.   \par \par \uc2 He added that the government had allocated a special Rp 90 billion ($1.06 million) fund to promote Indonesian tourism.   \par \par \uc2 However, Udin admitted that the new visa \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could be a bitter pill for the tourism industry. "If the government really wants to boost tourism, it should allow visa-free facilities to all countries."   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040113e01e00041\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
