\par\par \b \uc2 BI refuses to weaken rupiah to boost exports  \b0\par\par\uc2 Leony Aurora, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta  \par \uc2 443 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 February 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI) has refused to intervene in the foreign exchange market and weigh in on the rupiah performance against the U.S. dollar to boost exports in spite of calls from local business players.  \par \par \uc2 Speaking at an Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) business forum on Wednesday, BI governor Burhanuddin Abdullah said that exports should be increased through efficiency in the country's manufacturing sector.  \par \par \uc2 "Let's postpone the idea of disturbing rupiah to boost exports," he said in the opening session of the second day of the two-day forum.  \par \par \uc2 Indonesia is in desperate need for an increase in exports to accelerate its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, particularly as investment has remained weak due to various \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  both at home and overseas. The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth has been mainly driven by domestic consumption.  \par \par \uc2 Although last year's exports increased by 5.2 percent to US$61 billion from $57.2 billion in 2002, many experts believe that the figure could have gone higher had the rupiah not appreciated vis a vis the sliding greenback last year.  \par \par \uc2 The local unit now stands at around Rp 8,400 per U.S. dollar, about 6 percent stronger than its rate a year ago at Rp 8,900 per U.S. dollar. It was one of the best performing currencies in the region last year. The strengthening in the rupiah has been a major factor behind the overall stability in several of the country's key macroeconomic indicators.  \par \par \uc2 A sharp appreciation in the value of the rupiah can 