\par\par \b \uc2 IMF hails rising confidence in RI, but seeks further reform   \b0\par\par\uc2 Dadan Wijaksana , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 564 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 March 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The International Monetary Fund (IMF) said on Friday that the government had succeeded in retaining market confidence three months after the expiration of the Fund-backed special lending program.   \par \par \uc2 But the IMF also urged the government to press ahead with key reform programs, particularly in the areas of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , labor \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the legal system so as to further improve the business and investment climate in the country.   \par \par \uc2 The Fund cited the current macroeconomic stability and the successful launching of the government's US$1 billion international bond on Wednesday as evidence of improving market confidence in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "The successful sovereign bond issue just concluded is testimony to Indonesia's successful \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  performance over the past couple of years," the IMF said in a statement issued after the completion of its first review on the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  since the expiration of the IMF lending program late last year.   \par \par \uc2 A special team led by visiting IMF Senior Advisor for Asia Pacific Department Daniel Citrin has been conducting a 10-day review and consultation with the government, under a post-program monitoring (PPM) arrangement, a mandatory requirement for a member country having just graduated from an IMF loan program.   \par \par \uc2 Despite its non-binding nature, the review and assessment by the team is of major importance for the country as it represents a crucial indicator for measuring market sentiment on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Citrin told a press conference that going forward the government should push ahead with various reform programs, particularly in the areas of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 , law reform and labor law.   \par \par \uc2 "\b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  efforts should concentrate on these areas ... which are important for improving the business climate and laying the foundation for sustainable growth at a level that would reduce unemployment.   \par \par \uc2 "Because Indonesia's GDP growth and export performance as compared with other nations in the region have lagged behind," Citrin told journalists.   \par \par \uc2 During the visit, Citrin said the team discussed a wide range of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  issues with government officials and civil society organizations including labor unions, business people and academics.   \par \par \uc2 Lack of investment has been the main factor stalling the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, which has only managed to grow at a modest level of around 4 percent -- insufficient to absorb the some 2.5 million fresh job-seekers coming on the market every year.   \par \par \uc2 The government is targeting \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth this year of 4.8 percent.   \par \par \uc2 Citrin cited the first of three priorities, namely \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  administration and enforcement, as the main area of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  to business people. "This covers everything from \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  arbitration, the system and procedures, to inefficiency in the refund mechanism on VAT. There are many complaints over these."   \par \par \uc2 As for labor \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Citrin emphasized that it must be a balance between protecting labor and providing flexibility for employers. He did not elaborate on whether this meant the government should revise the existing labor law, which was enacted last year.   \par \par \uc2 The IMF said in a statement that at present the country's total outstanding debt to the Fund amounted to $10 billion. The current PPM program will expire when Indonesia's outstanding debt falls below $3 billion -- the lending quota for an IMF member country.   \par \par \uc2 Indonesia asked the IMF to bail it out in 1999 after the country was rocked by the regional financial crisis.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040305e0360000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
