\par\par \b \uc2 Activists ask Megawati to revoke mining decree  \b0\par\par\uc2 Kurniawan Hari , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta  \par \uc2 477 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 March 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 4\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 A group of environmental activists and economists called on the government on Monday to revoke the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in lieu of law (perpu) that allows 13 mining companies to resume activities in protected forests, saying their operations would cause more \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  losses and environmental damage.  \par \par \uc2 They also called on the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is now in recess, to reject the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  President Megawati Soekarnoputri issued two weeks ago.  \par \par \uc2 Article 22 of the newly amended Constitution stipulates that the president may issue such a \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in an emergency situation.  \par \par \uc2 It must, however, win the approval of a House plenary meeting, otherwise it must be revoked.  \par \par \uc2 "The perpu contains procedural and substantial flaws and should be revoked," Indonesian Biodiversity Foundation (Kehati) director Ismid Hadad told The Jakarta Post here on Monday.  \par \par \uc2 Megawati issued two weeks ago Perpu No. 1/2004, which allows 13 mining companies in protected forests to resume their activities.  \par \par \uc2 The 13 mining companies were part of some two dozen mining firms operating in protected forests that froze their operations following enactment of new forestry \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 1999.  \par \par \uc2 The law, which banned opencast mining in protected forests, made no mention of contracts signed before it was enacted, creating \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  for mining companies already operating in protected forests.  \par \par \uc2 The legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  forced the companies to either freeze or scale down their operations.  \par \par \uc2 Article 38(A) of Perpu No.1/2004 stipulates that all licenses and contracts for mining business in forests signed before the enactment of the Forestry Law were valid for the remainder of the original term of the license or contract.  \par \par \uc2 Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Dorodjatun Kuntjoro-Jakti said the 13 mining companies would be allowed to resume their activities because they had proven \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  that were economically viable.  \par \par \uc2 Also on Monday, a group of nongovernmental organization (NGOs) activists and economists criticized the issuance of the new \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which they said would only worsen environmental destruction.  \par \par \uc2 They included economist Dradjad H. Wibowo, Indonesian Forum for the Environment (Walhi) director Longgena Ginting, Worldwide Fund for Nature (WWF) official Mubariq Achmad and Advocacy Network for Mining (JATAM) coordinator Siti Maimunah.  \par \par \uc2 They said in a statement that Megawati had issued the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  without providing proper information and justification to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 They added that issuance of the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  clearly showed that the President had no commitment to conserving the depleting forest.  \par \par \uc2 They alleged that Indonesia's forests had been decreasing by about 3.8 million hectares per year, causing the state to lose some Rp 30 trillion annually.  \par \par \uc2 Legislator M. Askin revealed that House Commission VIII for environmental issues had told the government to study the possibility of allowing mining activities in protected forests.  \par \par \uc2 "The perpu was issued before the government completed its study, so I think the House will not approve it," he said.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040315e03g0000i\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
