ia still needed more investment to further boost the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said.   \par \par \uc2 During the past few years it had been growing at a "mediocre" rate of about 4 percent due to poor investment and sluggish exports.   \par \par \uc2 The government has set a growth target of 4.8 percent this year. A healthy investment market is crucial for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth necessary to create sufficient jobs for millions of unemployed people.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, BKPM deputy head Yus'an said local administrations would still be given freedom under the regional autonomy \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to manage investments in their own territories.   \par \par \uc2 "It will be better, however, if there is a concerted coordination and cooperation between the administrations and the central government," he said.   \par \par \uc2 The cooperation, explained Yus'an, would include the provision of information and promotional materials, the identification of areas with investment potential, and the creation of favorable conditions.   \par \par \uc2 The latter should include the abolishment of local regulations which could inhibit investment.   \par \par \uc2 The government is also preparing several other policies to promote investment in the country.   \par \par \uc2 These include the drafting of a new, unified investment law to replace Law No. 1/1967 on foreign investment and Law No. 6/1968 on domestic investment, as well as the setting up of a "one-tier" investment service system.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040316e03h00005\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
