\par\par \b \uc2 Jakarta stocks increase slightly on bargain hunting   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 472 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 April 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Shares on the Jakarta stock market ended slightly higher on Tuesday on a technical rebound as investors snapped up stocks after profit taking in the previous trading sessions, a stock analyst said.   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Stock Composite Index closed higher by 3.927 points, or 0.5 percent, at 771.739, on volume of 995.98 million shares worth Rp 541.33 billion (US$63 million). Gainers led losers 59 to 48, while 83 stocks were unchanged.   \par \par \uc2 Shares of heavyweight state-owned telecommunications company PT Telekomunikasi Indonesia (Telkom) led the gain with a 1.3 percent surge, or Rp 100, to Rp 7,900. Telkom is the largest counter on the JSX with around 17 percent of market capitalization.   \par \par \uc2 Bank Central Asia (BCA), the country's third largest lender in terms of assets, gained Rp 75 to close at Rp 3,750, and Bank Danamon rose by Rp 125 to Rp 3,225. Cigarette maker PT Gudang Garam was up Rp 50 at Rp 13,300.   \par \par \uc2 "There has been no significant news for the bourse. The rise is mainly caused by bargain hunting on selected bluechips after profit taking on Monday," said stock analyst Edy S. Widjojo of Ciptadana Securities.   \par \par \uc2 He said that the gains made on Tuesday might encourage other investors to buy shares over the next couple of days. However, investors were also not ruling out the possibility of profit-taking following the gains.   \par \par \uc2 Edy, however, said that the overall sentiment in the market would remain gloomy for the next couple of weeks on fears of political instability following news that a number of politicians and parties might reject the results of the general election.   \par \par \uc2 "Political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  will overshadow the stock market in the coming days." he said.   \par \par \uc2 Concerns about the outcome of the general election as well as the slow ballot counting process, and how it will affect the upcoming presidential election on July 5, have worried some investors.   \par \par \uc2 The situation has been further exacerbated by the recent move by 17 of the 24 political parties contesting this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  election to reject the poll results, and their demand for the General Elections Commission (KPU) to hold the election again due to what they claimed was endemic vote-rigging.   \par \par \uc2 Gains in a number of benchmark global stock markets due to growing \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence have helped reduce the distress on the JSX.   \par \par \uc2 In Japan, the Tokyo Stock Exchange's benchmark Nikkei-225 index gained 0.71 percent or 85.12 points to close at 12,127.82, its highest since August 2001.   \par \par \uc2 In Hong Kong, the Hang Seng Index rose 122.44 points to 13,031.81.   \par \par \uc2 Elsewhere, the rupiah was at Rp 8,590 against the U.S. dollar on Tuesday, up from Rp 8,595 on Monday.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040413e04e00010\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
