\par\par \b \uc2 Rupiah and  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 742 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 May 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The move by Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  last week to significantly raise the ceiling \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on time deposits under the blanket guarantee scheme should be welcomed as a correct and timely measure to save the rupiah exchange rate from wild volatility.   \par \par \uc2 Indeed, with two of the world's largest economies -- the United States and China-- about to tighten their monetary policies to ward off inflation, countries like Indonesia that greatly depend on the export market for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth should make the necessary adjustments.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  early last week raised the ceiling \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on one-month to two-year time deposits from a range of 6.11 percent to 6.18 percent, to 7.25 percent to 7.80 percent, under the government's blanket guarantee program. This move gives banks more leeway to increase the \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  they can offer depositors.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah fell to as low as Rp 8,734.50 against the U.S. dollar last week, slightly below the floor of the Rp 8,200 to Rp 8,700 range, or the comfort zone, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has pledged to maintain for the local unit.   \par \par \uc2 A combination of internal factors -- security disturbances in Maluku, Makassar and Riau -- and external factors, notably the tighter money \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  imposed by China and strong speculation of a similar monetary move in the U.S, which strengthened the American dollar, were responsible for the negative sentiment on the rupiah.   \par \par \uc2 Even though the U.S. Federal Reserve has yet to raise its funds rate, something that has been widely predicted by financial market analysts over the last two months, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's decision last week was nevertheless the right move. Almost all pundits have predicted a rise in the Fed's funds rate as inevitable, saying it is only a matter of time. Many expect it in June, while some other analysts foresee such a move in August.   \par \par \uc2 Obviously, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  cannot make its interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  independent from its exchange rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . If the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  is committed to maintaining the rupiah in its "comfort zone", it consequently must raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  in anticipation of the Fed rate hike, otherwise many big depositors may shift to dollar positions.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is right in asserting that the weakening of the rupiah is only a temporary phenomenon that will soon pass because the fundamentals of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  remain strong.   \par \par \uc2 Movements in financial markets rarely reflect changes in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals, because they are based on the market perception of what is likely to happen and this perception is formed mainly by the information market players currently have.   \par \par \uc2 The perception now is that the American dollar will strengthen because of the upcoming move to be taken by the Federal Reserve to tighten its monetary stance to ward off inflation. Without adjustments to its domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the rupiah may come under attacks because many depositors may realign the composition of their deposits in favor of the greenback.   \par \par \uc2 Even last week's monetary measure now makes it possible for commercial banks to raise their deposit rates to as high as 7 percent, most major banks will most likely maintain their rates at their current range of 5.5 percent to 5.7 percent because they are still awash with excess liquidity.   \par \par \uc2 Just see how the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has steadily lowered its benchmark interest rate on certificates of deposit from as high as 8.3 percent early this year to 7.32 percent last week, and yet commercial banks remain hesitant to accelerate the pace of their corporate lending due to the high risk of credit turning sour.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  that will remain until the country's elections are completed in September further adds to the banks' overly cautious stance on lending.   \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's latest monthly report showed that as of March, commercial banks' outstanding balance in such \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  open-market instruments as SBIs remained quite high at more than Rp 155 trillion (US$18.3 billion). Most analysts estimate that the loan to deposit ratio within the banking industry is hovering at about 50 percent. As long as the SBI rate remains much higher than deposit rates, banks will not feel compelled to expand their lending.   \par \par \uc2 We therefore see this latest monetary measure by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  more as a preemptive move to protect the rupiah against speculative attacks, rather than an attempt to prod banks into raising their deposit rates.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040510e05b0000t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
