\par\par \b \uc2 Rupiah woe may loom for long, BI undeterred  \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular, Jakarta  \par \uc2 785 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 May 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 While acknowledging that the rupiah's woes may last longer due to the global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  at present, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  remains confident that it will eventually stabilize as the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals remain strong.  \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  deputy governor Anwar Nasution said on Friday that once the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  abated, the rupiah would return to its "comfort level" of between Rp 8,300 and Rp 8,700 against the U.S. dollar. It closed on Friday at Rp 9,065.  \par \par \uc2 "Inflation remains under control, our banking industry is also improving, and our foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  are sufficient to help support the rupiah. So what are we afraid of?" Anwar said during a weekly press conference.  \par \par \uc2 "It is just a temporary decline, other countries are also suffering from the same problem. It is just the global sentiment, and it will gradually abate," he added.  \par \par \uc2 He said that there was no reason for the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to increase its benchmark interest rate despite the falling rupiah and a planned hike in the U.S. rate.  \par \par \uc2 He pointed out that the real interest rate level of around 2 percent at home was still relatively higher than the rates overseas.  \par \par \uc2 Such a competitive rate means that there is actually room for a further cut in domestic interest rate, he added.  \par \par \uc2 The real interest rate figure is obtained by subtracting the current \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month benchmark interest rate of 7.32 percent from the annual inflation level of more than 5 percent.  \par \par \uc2 "It must have been a stupid move by investors to pull out their money from Indonesia, or to convert their rupiah-denominated assets to dollar-denominated ones, since our real \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  are more competitive than those of other countries," said Anwar.  \par \par \uc2 The rupiah has lost more than 4 percent against the dollar since the beginning of this month due to a combination of external factors such as a possible hike in the U.S. interest rate, surging oil prices and a possible sharp \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown in China as it struggles to tighten controls on its rapidly expanding \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . On the domestic front, political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  leading up to the upcoming presidential election has also created pressure on rupiah.  \par \par \uc2 BI has placed the blame on four international banks based here, which have allegedly used the market's weak sentiment to speculate against the rupiah, driving the unit to its 14-month low recently. BI last week issued warning letters to the four banks over the practices.  \par \par \uc2 Although unconfirmed, several local newspapers have reported that the four banks are Standard Chartered Bank, ABN Amro, Deutsche Bank and JP Morgan.  \par \par \uc2 Anwar said that the warning letters were not against the free-flow of foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , since the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had the obligation to control the rupiah from fluctuating sharply, a condition which would disturb the country's overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 "The four banks are now still in the process of investigation. The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has the authority to stabilize the rupiah so that it will not go up and down drastically like a fever," he said.  \par \par \uc2 Ruster  \par \par \uc2 ;JP;REN; ANPAf..r.. Stock-rupiah-market JP/ /  \par \par \uc2 Stock ends higher, rupiah slumps  \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta stock market rose by 2.57 percent on Friday for the third straight trading session on bargain hunting in some shares and subsiding concern over interest rate hikes in the United States.  \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Stock Composite Index ended 18.135 points higher at 724.932 on volume of 1.09 billion shares worth Rp 1.08 trillion (US$120 million).  \par \par \uc2 State-run telecommunications firm PT Telkom led the rally in bluechips as it ended higher by Rp 150 to Rp 7,500. Its rival PT Indosat was also up by Rp 225 to Rp 3,800.  \par \par \uc2 Cigarette producer PT Gudang Garam gained Rp 400 to Rp 13,650, its rival PT Sampoerna also surged by Rp 150 to Rp 5,000. Automotive kingpin PT Astra International ended higher by Rp 100 to Rp 5,800, and Bank Mandiri was up Rp 50 to Rp 1,250.  \par \par \uc2 Analysts said that foreign investors made up more than 50 percent of the transactions, as many stocks were already considered cheap following massive losses last week.  \par \par \uc2 Elsewhere, the rupiah failed to track the gains in the stock market, as it closed lower again to Rp 9,065 per U.S. dollar from Rp 9,050 on Wednesday.  \par \par \uc2 Analysts said the decline was mostly driven by panic buying from the corporate sectors as they feared that the rupiah's depreciation would last for a long period of time, thus burdening their costs for importing raw materials and repaying dollar-denominated debts. -- JP  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040521e05m0000b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
