\par\par \b \uc2 Rupiah fall only temporary: Govt   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 571 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 May 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah fell to a 19-month low on Tuesday as \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  created jitters among companies, which lately have been heavy buyers of dollars.   \par \par \uc2 But Minister of Finance Boediono said the rupiah's fall was only temporary as the large current account \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the U.S. would eventually push the American greenback lower.   \par \par \uc2 "In my opinion, this is only a short-lived trend. In fact, in the medium-term, the dollar will weaken," he said.   \par \par \uc2 He added that as part of efforts to help stabilize the local unit, the government would dispose of its dollar-based assets. He did not provide details, but a Ministry of Finance official said that part of the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue was in dollar notes.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah closed at Rp 9,260 against the dollar on Tuesday, lower than Monday's close of Rp 9,125. The local unit plunged to as low as Rp 9,345 during the day, but dealers said that intervention by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  helped to prevent the rupiah from a deeper plunge.   \par \par \uc2 They added that expectation of a hike in U.S. interest rate later next month, soaring oil prices, and domestic political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the July 5 presidential election had prompted local corporations to purchase dollars as they feared the local unit might fall further. The companies need the hard currency to repay maturing overseas debts and finance the import of raw materials.   \par \par \uc2 Expectations the U.S. Federal Reserve will hike \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  from their 46-year low have prompted investors to switch their investment to dollar-based assets, which, in the case of Indonesia, harmed the rupiah.   \par \par \uc2 But remarks from Boediono suggest that the fall in the rupiah, which has been the worst-performing currency in the Asia region so far this year, is not a sign of the reemergence of the late 1990s currency crisis, given particularly the country's stronger foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and more stable macroeconomic conditions.   \par \par \uc2 Nevertheless, the fall in the local unit, especially as the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  seems to be unable to stem its decline, has created fears of inflationary pressures at home, and might force the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to start pushing domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  higher, both of which could harm the overall \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the fall in the local unit contributed to a 2.1 percent decline in the Jakarta Stock Composite Index to 717.13 points on Tuesday. The index has fallen 12 percent since its April 27 high.   \par \par \uc2 Falls in many Asian stock markets also affected the local market.   \par \par \uc2 But traders said that late bargain-hunting in select blue chips lifted the index from its intraday low. Decliners led gainers 101 to 25, with 37 stocks unchanged. Volume was 1.1 billion shares valued at Rp 764 billion.   \par \par \uc2 Bellwether PT Telkom lost Rp 350, or 4.6 percent, to Rp 7,250 on profit-taking, and after its American Depositary Receipts fell 0.5 percent to US$16.86 on Monday.   \par \par \uc2 Select banking blue chips ended lower on renewed worries that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  may increase \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to pr