\par\par \b \uc2 Govt, House may delay state firm privatization  \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular , Jakarta  \par \uc2 578 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 May 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 The government may delay the sale of shares in a number of state-owned firms, including giant Bank Mandiri, this year, due to current \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the financial market, according to a senior official.  \par \par \uc2 "Mandiri is still on the list for privatization. Timing is very important during this process. We may delay it until next year if the market remains unsuitable," said Mahmuddin Yasin, deputy for privatization at the Office of the State Minister of State Enterprises, after a closed-door meeting on Thursday with the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  subcommission overseeing the privatization program.  \par \par \uc2 The government plans to sell 10 percent of its stake in Mandiri in the second semester of this year.  \par \par \uc2 At present, the government holds a 70 percent stake in the bank, after successfully selling a 20 percent shareholding via an initial \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offering (IPO) last year, and another 10 percent in a secondary offering in March of this year.  \par \par \uc2 But Mahmuddin refused to confirm whether the delay in the privatization program would cause the government to be unable to meet this year's privatization proceeds target of Rp 5 trillion, which is crucial to help finance the 2004 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 So far this year, the government raised around Rp 3.6 trillion from the sale of a 10 percent stake in Mandiri in March, and the sale of shares in small consultancy companies.  \par \par \uc2 The local capital market has been on a roller-coaster ride during the past few weeks, sending the rupiah tumbling to a 19-month low, and stocks falling by 12 percent from a historical high in April as investors switched from rupiah-based to dollar-based assets amid expectations of a rise in U.S. interest rate, and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  here.  \par \par \uc2 This \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  has also forced the government to cancel a planned Rp 3.5 trillion bond issue on Tuesday as investors demanded overly high yields due to the rising \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, lawmaker Muchtar Noerdjaya, who heads the House subcommission, said that the House might also issue a recommendation for a delay in this year's privatization program due to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  both at home and globally.  \par \par \uc2 "We will discuss with the government next week the possibility of delaying some privatization programs," Muchtar told The Jakarta Post following the meeting.  \par \par \uc2 "Timing is the most important factor that must be taken into consideration. We don't wish to sell state assets and obtain small returns. It's better to delay the program at the moment, pending better market conditions," said Muchtar.  \par \par \uc2 The government has planned to sell state companies under this year's privatization program through various schemes, such as private placement to strategic investors, IPOs and secondary \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  offerings.  \par \par \uc2 The companies to be sold this year include pharmaceutical companies PT Kimia Farma and PT Indo Farma, where a majority stake will be sold through private placement to strategic investors.  \par \par \uc2 IPOs are planned for fertilizer producer PT Pupuk Kaltim and state plantation firms PT Perkebunan Nusantara III, IV and V.  \par \par \uc2 Shares in gold and nickel producer PT Aneka Tambang, tin producer PT Timah, coal producer PT Tambang Batubara Bukit Asam, Bank Mandiri and Bank Rakyat Indonesia will also be offered through secondary market offerings.  \par \par \uc2 Also to be put on offer are shares in national flag-carrier Garuda Indonesia, airline operator Merpati Nusantara, port operators PT Angkasa Pura II (Soekarno-Hatta International Airport, Jakarta) and PT Angkasa Pura I.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040527e05s00013\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
