\par\par \b \uc2 Job creation tops the list of Mega's  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  platform   \b0\par\par\uc2 Zakki P. Hakim, Jakarta   \par \uc2 535 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 June 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 President Megawati Soekarnoputri and her running mate, Hasyim Muzadi, promise to create millions of new jobs in the next five years if she gets reelected for a second term in the upcoming election.   \par \par \uc2 But critics have said that this is an area where she has generally failed so far.   \par \par \uc2 In a document describing the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  platform of the pair, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is envisaged to grow by an average of 6.8 percent per year, peaking at 7.9 percent in 2009, in order to create some 12.9 million jobs during the five-year period. This, in turn, is expected to significantly resolve pressing unemployment problems.   \par \par \uc2 Although the current Megawati administration has been applauded by many for successfully stabilizing the country's macroeconomic indicators such as inflation and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it has failed to transform this into higher \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, mainly due to a lack of fresh investment amid lingering legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , corruption and security problems.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been growing at a mediocre rate of around 4 percent during the past couple of years, mainly driven by domestic consumption. \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth needs to accelerate to 6 percent to 7 percent per year in order to create sufficient jobs for the millions of unemployed. Higher investment is crucial to the acceleration of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.   \par \par \uc2 High unemployment has been the most pressing problem since the country tumbled into an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in the late 1990s. The country's open unemployment figure is around 10.5 million, while people living below the poverty line total around 40 million (of the country's 220 million population).   \par \par \uc2 But Megawati is confident that investment will return.   \par \par \uc2 "Most of the investment would be financed from domestic sources," stated the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  platform document, adding that to achieve the above growth target, a huge investment of around 27.1 percent of gross domestic product (GDP) would be needed.   \par \par \uc2 According to the document, the unemployment rate is projected to fall to 6.3 percent in 2009 from last year's 9.5 percent.   \par \par \uc2 As part of a job creation program, the Megawati-Hasyim duo will also empower small and medium-scale enterprises by providing easier access to bank loans, with priority in the eastern part of Indonesia.   \par \par \uc2 The pair also sees the agriculture sector as playing a dominant role in absorbing unemployment and plans an average 2.8 percent growth in this sector, compared with the 2.1 percent realized from 2001 to 2003.   \par \par \uc2 The Megawati government plans incentives for farmers.   \par \par \uc2 Apart from job creation, other agenda items that top the list in Megawati's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  platform are maintaining \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability and improving the international competitiveness of the local \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The government's debt level will be reduced to 32.8 percent of GDP in 2009 from this year's estimate of 64.4 percent.   \par \par \uc2 Reducing the debt will involve an attempt to trim the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  by strengthening \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainability through higher \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue, new foreign debt management and efficiency in government expenses.   \par \par \uc2 Despite the controversy on Indonesian workers abroad, the pair supports the sending of more workers as a solution to help improve conditions for the domestic workforce.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040531e0610000b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
