\par\par \b \uc2 May inflation creates new worries   \b0\par\par\uc2 Dadan Wijaksana, Jakarta   \par \uc2 491 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 June 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Prices increased faster in May than in April due to the weakening rupiah and higher telephone charges, giving rise to concerns about inflation that could force the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to start raising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The Central Statistics Agency (BPS) reported on Tuesday that inflation in May rose by 6.47 percent from the same month last year, stronger than the year-on-year inflation rate of 5.29 percent in April.   \par \par \uc2 Compared to the previous month, inflation in May was up by 0.88 percent, the agency said.   \par \par \uc2 "The inflation increase in May was mainly due to rises in the cost of telecommunications, transportation and basic food prices," said BPS chairwoman Soedarti Surbakti during a press conference.   \par \par \uc2 Telecommunications company PT Telkom raised local phone charges by an average of 28 percent in April.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the drop in the value of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar has pushed up the cost of production for many companies as they are dependent on imported raw materials.   \par \par \uc2 The rupiah has fallen by 11 percent so far this year due to a combination of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home and overseas, and also political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the July presidential election. The local unit plunged to a 26-month low of Rp 9,380 per dollar on Tuesday.   \par \par \uc2 The BPS said that basic food prices rose by 0.55 percent in the month, while the cost of transportation and telecommunications was up by 3.88 percent.   \par \par \uc2 Other elements in the consumer price index (CPI) which also experienced price increases are processed food and beverages (up 0.21 percent), clothing (0.02 percent), health care (0.43 percent), and education and recreation (0.11 percent), the BPS said.   \par \par \uc2 Soedarti said that as the current weakening of the rupiah and soaring oil prices would continue to stoke up inflationary pressure in the months ahead, she predicted that inflation for the full year would surpass the government's 6.5 percent target.   \par \par \uc2 There have been increasing worries about the reemergence of stronger inflationary pressures in the local \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  particularly due to the weakening of the rupiah and rising oil prices.   \par \par \uc2 Stronger inflation could force the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to start raising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to both help curb inflation and defend the local unit, which has been badly affected by news that the U.S. Federal Reserve could start raising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  next month. As a result, investors have switched from rupiah assets to dollar-based assets.   \par \par \uc2 But \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the past weeks has been insisting that it had no plans to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  soon despite a hike in the U.S. rate. Raising domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  could harm the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.   \par \par \uc2 Some \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials have actually indicated that there was still room for the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  benchmark interest rate to decrease further to around 6 percent this year from the current level of around 7 percent.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040601e06200017\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\pi