\par\par \b \uc2 Miranda new BI senior deputy governor   \b0\par\par\uc2 Tony Hotland , Jakarta   \par \uc2 594 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 June 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Miranda Swaray Goeltom was named on Tuesday night as the new senior deputy governor of \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a key post which will have a greater role in determining \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies.   \par \par \uc2 The decision was made during a closed-door meeting at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Commission IX on financial affairs.   \par \par \uc2 Commission chairman Emir Moeis said that Miranda won 41 votes, while her rivals Sunaryo Budi Rochadi (head of the \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  office in Tokyo) got 12 votes and Hartadi Agus Sarwono (currently a deputy governor at \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) one vote.   \par \par \uc2 "Miranda was chosen because she has been quite clear in explaining her vision and mission ... She seems to be more capable," he announced publicly.   \par \par \uc2 The three made presentations at the commission during the day before the legislators started voting.   \par \par \uc2 Miranda will replace Anwar Nasution, whose five-year term will expire on July 27.   \par \par \uc2 In her presentation at the House, Miranda said that her top priority would be to seek ways to help stabilize the embattled rupiah.   \par \par \uc2 The local unit has dropped sharply against the U.S. dollar over the past month, due in large part to \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home as well as a possible hike in U.S. \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The continual slide is creating new worries about the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as it could eventually lead to stronger inflationary pressure and slower \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.   \par \par \uc2 Miranda first took a senior position at the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  in 1997 as a director, and two years later was elected deputy governor during a time when \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  first became an independent \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 But during her tenure at \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's reputation was at its lowest point, particularly after the way it handled the massive bank bailout during the late 1990s financial crisis, which according to the Supreme Audit Agency had been mostly abused by the banks. The taxpayers now have been asked to cover those trillions of rupiah in losses.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, three non-governmental organizations; Transparency International Indonesia, the Institute for Development of Economics and Finance (Indef) and the Professional Society all opposed the appointment of Miranda as well as the two other candidates, saying that none of them had the qualities in terms of integrity, expertise and experience as required by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  law.   \par \par \uc2 "BI needs a "super" senior deputy governor to handle the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems, as well as to monitor vulnerable banks and curb the rise in non-performing loans," Dradjad Wibowo of Indef told reporters in front of the Commission IX meeting room while the candidates were making their presentations.   \par \par \uc2 He said that they were demanding that the government cancel the selection process and come up with more qualified people. By law, the President proposes a list of candidates for the House to select.   \par \par \uc2 But Dradjat declined to mention any further details about the candidates' integrity, which has become a concern amid reports of bribes being exchanged in the selection process.   \par \par \uc2 Profile:   \par \par \uc2 Miranda Swaray Goeltom   \par \par \uc2 Born in Jakarta, June 19, 1949.   \par \par \uc2 Master's (1990) and Doctoral (1992) degrees in Economics from Boston University, USA. Bachelor's Degree in Economics from the University of Indonesia (1975).   \par \par \uc2 1993-1998: Assistant Deputy at the Office of Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Financial, and Developmental Supervision   \par \par \uc2 1997: Director at BI   \par \par \uc2 1998: President of PT Bank Uppindo   \par \par \uc2 A deputy governor of BI (May 1999) for a four-year term. President Megawati proposed her in 2003 to replace then BI Governor Sjahril Sabirin, but she lost to Burhanuddin Abdullah.   \par \par \uc2 2004-present: Chief Commissioner at RaboBank   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040608e06900002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
