\par\par \b \uc2 New government expected to maintain  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  course   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 540 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 June 2004\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2004 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Capital market analysts expect the new government, to be inaugurated later this year, to continue with the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies at least as far as \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary stability are concerned.   \par \par \uc2 Analyst Ferry Yosia Hartoyo of DBS Vickers Securities said on Monday that foreign investors, by and large, hoped the new government will maintain the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform programs that have been laid out in the "White Paper" document to prevent new risks to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 "The \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs of all the presidential candidates already include much of what is stated in the White Paper. Investors will recalculate their stance, however, if there are any drastic changes in \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said Ferry.   \par \par \uc2 The White Paper contains a series of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform targets the government must achieve in the 18-month period that began in August 2003. It was produced after the government made the decision not to extend the International Monetary Fund-sponsored \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program, which expired at the end of 2003.   \par \par \uc2 Among the key policies set out in the White Paper, are measures aimed at achieving and maintaining \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary stability. The current government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  have actually been credited by international donors with stabilizing the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation by cutting down the ratio of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  debt in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in relation to gross domestic product. It also calls for stabilizing the monetary indicators such as inflation and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , both of which skyrocketed in the wake of the late 1990s financial crisis.   \par \par \uc2 However, critics have said that the current government failed to take advantage of the positive sentiment in the wake of the White Paper's release, because investment remains scarce due a variety of negative factors, most notably legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a key area in the post-IMF reform program that has not been successful.   \par \par \uc2 Ferry said that in the short term, the new government would actually have a limited set of options, as they would have to finish the programs set out in the White Paper.   \par \par \uc2 He explained that such a continuation was needed since the White Paper had become a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  anchor on which international creditors and investors based their perceptions and calculations of Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook and investment risks.   \par \par \uc2 The head of the investment management division of Mandiri Securities, Sutomo, agreed with Ferry. Sutomo pointed out that the capital market players wanted a continuation of the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs, in a bid to prevent confusion and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  among investors.   \par \par \uc2 "The market just will not stand for any confusion resulting from a discontinuation of the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs, as it may jeopardize the current monetary and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability," said Sutomo.   \par \par \uc2 The five contesting presidential candidates (Wiranto, current President Megawati Soekarnoputri, Amien Rais, frontrunner Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono and Hamzah Haz) in the upcoming July 5 election have all put \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery at the top of their agenda.   \par \par \uc2 Stock analyst Hendra Bujang of Mega Access Securities said that aside from continuing the current programs, the next government should also focus on reviving the corporate sector, in order to push more companies to list their shares on the stock market, and to help the country to achieve higher, more sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020040614e06f00008\par }\par \b \uc2 Search Summary\b0\par \par  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx2000\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx9072\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Text\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \li50\uc2 (economic or economy) and (uncertain or uncertainty or uncertainties) and (policy or public or tax or taxation or taxes or taxed or spending or expenditure or fiscal or stimulus or budget or deficit or national debt or tariff or subsidies or subsidy or Bank Indonesia or central bank or reserves or interest rates or fiscal or legislation or legislative or house of representatives or regulation)\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx2000\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx9072\row } \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\brdrs\clbrdrb\brdrs\clbrdrr\brdrs \cellx2000\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\clbrdrl\br